1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:03,590
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,590 --> 00:00:06,780
The Alliance of Official 
Guilds vs. Oracion Seis!

3
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:10,030
During that fierce battle, 
Jellal was resurrected!

4
00:00:10,030 --> 00:00:11,430
I'm sorry...

5
00:00:11,430 --> 00:00:14,150
Erza, now recovered, goes and disappears...

6
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:17,120
And the seal locking away 
Nirvana has been unlocked!

7
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,680
I'm sorry...

8
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:28,670
If it's love and dreams and you it'll become magical.

9
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:35,840
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

10
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:48,770
I kind of admired this powerful world,

11
00:00:48,770 --> 00:00:53,190
chock-full of problems.

12
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:59,970
Frozen time has started to move again

13
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:05,580
ever since I met you.

14
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:11,000
Why were we born? Why do we live?

15
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,840
I don't need any complicated answers.

16
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:22,780
Laugh! Cry! Be honest with yourself.

17
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:27,560
Simple feelings are the most important.

18
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:35,900
You can change those tears shed on sad nights into strength.

19
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:42,530
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

20
00:01:50,790 --> 00:01:56,550
Erza and Jellal have finally reunited 
deep inside of the Worth Woodsea.

21
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:02,170
But Jellal has lost his memories.

22
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:15,350
Jellal is trying to free Erza of her hatred

23
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:23,390
by using self-destruction magic circles 
to destroy both Nirvana and himself.

24
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,080
However, Erza...

25
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:30,210
Jellal!

26
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:46,010
So you're gonna take the cancellation code 
for the magic circles to the grave with you?

27
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:50,520
I will not allow it! I won't 
allow you to die like this!

28
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,600
You have sins to repent for!

29
00:02:56,390 --> 00:03:00,470
Remember! Do you think you'll 
be at peace knowing nothing?

30
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:08,950
Live, and struggle!

31
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,700
Jellal!

32
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:17,980
March of Destruction!

33
00:03:25,270 --> 00:03:26,210
Erza...

34
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:30,230
Why... are you crying?

35
00:03:43,020 --> 00:03:44,490
You are so kind...

36
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:50,860
Jellal! You have to stay awake!

37
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,710
What is the meaning of this?

38
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,460
Brain.

39
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:04,050
A self-destruction magic circle?

40
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,680
Jellal constructed it, that bastard!

41
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:12,200
This is bad! At this rate, we'll have 
finally found Nirvana only to see it destroyed!

42
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,110
Worry not, Cobra.

43
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:23,590
I'm sure you know just why 
I have the codename "Brain."

44
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:28,170
I was once a member of the 
Ministry of Magical Development.

45
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:33,960
During that time I used my knowledge 
to create hundreds of new spells.

46
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:38,940
One of them is the 
self-destruction magic circle.

47
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:41,630
And I was the one that taught you it.

48
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:46,300
Or have you forgotten, Jellal?

49
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,220
This area will do.

50
00:04:58,210 --> 00:05:01,480
Concentrate. Do it exactly as I taught you.

51
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:05,610
Illustrate the destruction you 
desire from within your head...

52
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:06,990
I know.

53
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:31,550
And after only telling him once...

54
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:41,190
To be able to master the self-destruction 
magic circle to this level is impressive, as always.

55
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,350
It isn't enough...

56
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:45,350
What?

57
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:52,730
What I desire is perfect destruction that 
leaves not even a speck of dust remaining.

58
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:57,700
He's...

59
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:11,930
Using a self-destruction magic 
circle on your own body?

60
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:15,500
So you are planning on dying 
along with the cancellation code?

61
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:19,160
It seems his memories are screwed up, 
thanks to the effects of Ethernano.

62
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:23,210
Basically, he doesn't realize he's a bad guy.

63
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:28,230
What? Hilarious!

64
00:06:31,330 --> 00:06:33,580
Even without the cancellation code...

65
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:41,030
...I can nullify the magic 
circle itself, you see.

66
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,800
No!

67
00:06:58,890 --> 00:07:01,170
How pitiful, Jellal!

68
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:04,440
Nirvana will be mine!

69
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:08,440
Never!

70
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:11,530
Awaken, Nirvana!

71
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:14,280
Erza!

72
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,530
Reveal yourself!

73
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:25,100
I can hear it! Our future!

74
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:27,870
The sound of the extinction of the light!

75
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:33,310
Jellal!

76
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,630
Erza!

77
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,150
Carla, look!

78
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:43,570
No... It can't be...

79
00:07:43,810 --> 00:07:46,480
Hot Eye-dono, what is that?

80
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:52,860
It has begun! The final stage... 
The resurrection of Nirvana!

81
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:55,400
Men!

82
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:57,530
What in the world is that?

83
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:59,910
We were too late?

84
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:01,570
What the...?!

85
00:08:01,570 --> 00:08:03,600
Whoa there, that's...

86
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,420
I-I think we're in trouble...

87
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:09,290
Damn it! Erza was inside that light!

88
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:10,560
Oh, no!

89
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,860
I've never smelled anything 
so dangerous as this!

90
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,850
Hot Eye-dono... Can you see something?

91
00:08:18,110 --> 00:08:22,360
Something... Something huge is coming, yes...

92
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:24,130
Something huge?

93
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:47,220
What in the world is this? I don't get it!

94
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:49,770
It's coming out of the ground around here!

95
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:51,940
So <i>this</i> is what Nirvana is?

96
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:54,290
Can you even call it "magic" at this point?

97
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:57,090
Whoa, the ground's shaking...

98
00:08:57,090 --> 00:08:58,820
Does anyone hear cracking?

99
00:08:58,820 --> 00:09:01,600
I have a really, <i>really </i>
bad feeling about this...

100
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,910
No kidding.

101
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:07,400
I called it!

102
00:09:10,810 --> 00:09:15,110
H-Hey! Hold it right there, you people!

103
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:22,890
Carla!

104
00:09:22,890 --> 00:09:24,370
Let's go, Wendy!

105
00:09:24,370 --> 00:09:25,360
Right!

106
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:29,230
Look, Carla!

107
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:30,300
That's...

108
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,770
That's...

109
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,620
...Nirvana?

110
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,710
Finally! Finally it is mine!

111
00:10:11,330 --> 00:10:14,100
The ultimate weapon that 
will destroy the light!

112
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:17,460
The ultra-inversion magic, Nirvana!

113
00:10:17,460 --> 00:10:21,960
The greatest weapons of the official 
guilds, their unity and trust...

114
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:25,520
...have now become powerless before me!

115
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,230
Erza...

116
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:40,990
Undo the self-destruction magic 
you cast on your own body!

117
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:46,220
You have a duty to survive!

118
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:53,580
I... wasn't able to stop Nirvana...

119
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:08,170
It's... all over...

120
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,970
What is over? Take a look.

121
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:25,410
Go, Fairy Tail!

122
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:27,840
You are the only ones who can stop this!

123
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:31,500
Carla, let's head over there!

124
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:32,120
Right!

125
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,940
Let's get up there as well!

126
00:11:33,940 --> 00:11:35,830
Yes. Take my hand, please.

127
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:39,210
Helping each other, as allies!

128
00:11:39,210 --> 00:11:42,470
This indeed is love! Yes...

129
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:47,720
We will not give up.

130
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,430
Our hopes are already connected.

131
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:54,020
We'll run up these and then 
bust up the main body!

132
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:57,390
By the way, why are you 
guys in matching outfits?

133
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:59,190
Don't ask me!

134
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:04,180
Live, and grab the future in front of you.

135
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,130
Jellal...

136
00:12:10,660 --> 00:12:13,150
Let's go... Together...

137
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,080
Yes...

138
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,430
Men?

139
00:12:46,990 --> 00:12:49,540
W-Where am I?

140
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:53,100
Where did those young 
whippersnappers run off to?

141
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:54,990
What's going on!?

142
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:58,080
Men!!

143
00:13:42,170 --> 00:13:44,500
What do you think you're doing, Natsu?

144
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:47,340
Get it together already, 'kay?

145
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:49,460
This thing's... You know, <i>that</i>...

146
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:50,330
That?

147
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:53,010
It's t-transportation, right?

148
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:55,970
It's moving, but it's not transportation!

149
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:57,270
Think of it like that!

150
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,270
Got it!

151
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:12,310
I-I'm gonna hurl...

152
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:17,390
These are octopus legs! You're 
okay riding animals, right?

153
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,870
There ain't any octopus in the forest...

154
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:22,080
Stop sweating the details!

155
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:26,700
Okay! I'm fine now!

156
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:31,800
Idiot! Don't let it get to you!

157
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,470
I know! Leave it to me!

158
00:14:47,740 --> 00:14:48,940
Natsu!

159
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,320
Happy!

160
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,380
Aye!

161
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:08,170
Happy! Nice catch!

162
00:15:09,170 --> 00:15:11,840
Man, that guy's gonna 
give me a heart attack...

163
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:16,540
That was too cool, my hero!

164
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:22,480
How about it, Natsu? Becoming the 
wind with me feels pretty good, huh?

165
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:33,810
Yeah! It's totally awesome!

166
00:15:33,810 --> 00:15:36,070
You guys head to the top like that!

167
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:39,310
We're going inside that hole over there!

168
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:40,070
Right!

169
00:15:40,070 --> 00:15:41,410
Aye, sir!

170
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:54,270
It's a city... And it looks really old.

171
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,700
I-I don't get it.

172
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,130
This smell...

173
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:04,900
It's his smell!

174
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:12,890
Finally, Brain! We've gotten Nirvana!

175
00:16:14,860 --> 00:16:17,790
So this is a relic of the ancients?

176
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:20,780
Cubellios, this is pretty awesome!

177
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:23,460
Look, Cobra.

178
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:26,710
Look at the world spread out below me.

179
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,410
The city of the ancients...

180
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:41,310
That itself is the true identity of Nirvana!

181
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:50,320
While I stand here on the King's Summit, 
this city moves exactly as I will it!

182
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:56,190
Move? Are we making it go somewhere?

183
00:16:56,190 --> 00:17:01,290
I'm aiming for a certain guild, you see...

184
00:17:02,180 --> 00:17:03,940
Our first target?

185
00:17:04,210 --> 00:17:07,940
Call it the first land to 
have its light extinguished.

186
00:17:11,090 --> 00:17:13,670
Go forth, ancient city!

187
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,030
Change our darkness for the light!

188
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:27,760
I'm gonna stop ya!

189
00:17:33,330 --> 00:17:34,280
It's you!

190
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:43,910
Roar of the Fire Dragon!

191
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:51,920
Cobra! Don't let him interfere!

192
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:54,190
Right! Cubellios!

193
00:17:59,810 --> 00:18:04,010
You! I'll burn everything!

194
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:14,070
Thank you, Happy!

195
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:15,540
Aye...

196
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:16,780
Why, that...

197
00:18:23,650 --> 00:18:26,520
What's that? The snake is flying!

198
00:18:27,260 --> 00:18:33,030
Hey. I heard that you couldn't 
handle transportation...

199
00:18:33,030 --> 00:18:35,020
Happy isn't transportation!

200
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:37,040
That's right!

201
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,520
I see.

202
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:41,440
So that's why you were already flying.

203
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:44,910
Because you aren't able to stand on Nirvana.

204
00:18:44,910 --> 00:18:46,620
You're a riot, buddy.

205
00:18:46,620 --> 00:18:48,810
That's none of your business, jerk!

206
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:53,020
Move it, 'cause I'm stopping 
this big pile of junk!

207
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:55,490
Go ahead and try.

208
00:18:55,490 --> 00:18:57,690
I won't let you get near Brain.

209
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:58,910
Brain?

210
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,280
So he's the one that's moving it?

211
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:06,580
Come, Dragon Slayer!

212
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:08,500
Comin' right at ya!

213
00:19:10,210 --> 00:19:13,690
...Pretend like that, but aim for that guy!

214
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:14,670
Aye!

215
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:24,490
A-Again and again...

216
00:19:24,490 --> 00:19:26,420
He totally predicted your moves!

217
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,560
I can hear your movements!

218
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,440
What?

219
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:37,370
Yes, that's better. Let's play.

220
00:19:50,770 --> 00:19:52,470
I'm sorry, Carla.

221
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:54,780
I shouldn't have pushed you...

222
00:19:54,780 --> 00:19:56,930
Don't worry about me.

223
00:19:56,930 --> 00:20:02,760
Anyway... What are you planning 
to do now that we're here?

224
00:20:06,350 --> 00:20:08,360
Are you still chasing after Jellal?

225
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:09,100
No!

226
00:20:10,670 --> 00:20:12,010
Wendy...

227
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:17,150
Well, maybe a little.

228
00:20:19,230 --> 00:20:22,820
But I have to stop this 
thing, no matter what.

229
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:27,870
There's got to be something 
even I can do, right?

230
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:32,540
Yes, you're right...

231
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,690
What's the matter, Carla?

232
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:57,100
It couldn't be... This has 
to be a coincidence, right?

233
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,040
This shouldn't be...

234
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:13,160
What is wrong, Carla?

235
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:17,050
It's where we're heading...

236
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:24,750
Our guild, Caitshelter, is dead 
ahead, right in this thing's path!

237
00:21:42,150 --> 00:21:45,760
Damn it! I can't hit him with anything!

238
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:48,820
I wonder what kind of magic he uses?

239
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:55,730
I have to finish this creep off quick, 
or I'll never be able to get at that guy!

240
00:21:57,100 --> 00:22:02,310
Let's go, Happy... We'll kick both their 
asses and stop this huge pile of junk!

241
00:22:02,310 --> 00:22:02,960
Aye!

242
00:22:03,390 --> 00:22:09,790
Not gonna happen. You guys will 
never be able to crush our wish!

243
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:13,430
Now, I'm going to enjoy this...

244
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:21,570
Damn you! I'm getting fired up!

245
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:59,380
Natsu! It's a snake, but 
it has wings and is flying!

246
00:23:59,380 --> 00:24:01,300
It's totally ripping off my character!

247
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:03,150
No, not really.

248
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:06,660
Whatever, just get him! Get him 
for ripping off my character!

249
00:24:06,660 --> 00:24:10,350
Hold it... Wouldn't Carla 
be more of a rip-off?

250
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:13,530
Carla can rip me off all she wants.

251
00:24:13,530 --> 00:24:16,880
Next time: Super Aerial 
Battle! Natsu vs. Cobra!

252
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,690
I think the snake's actually 
cooler. It has venom.

253
00:24:19,690 --> 00:24:21,600
But I have fish!

254
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,560
And fish helps... how exactly?

255
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:25,780


